# Slate — environment / secrets setup
#
# Slate runs on Cloudflare Workers, so secrets are handled the Cloudflare way,
# not via a plain .env file.
#
# 1) Get a FREE Gemini API key (no card required):
#      https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# 2) LOCAL DEV — create a file named `.dev.vars` in the project root (already
#    gitignored) with this line:
#
#      GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=your-key-here
#
# 3) PRODUCTION — set it as a Cloudflare secret (run once, it prompts for the value):
#
#      npx wrangler secret put GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY
#
# Optional model overrides (defaults are free-tier friendly). Bump the tutor to
# a Pro model (e.g. gemini-3.1-pro) for sharper reasoning once you add billing:
#
#      SLATE_TUTOR_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash
#      SLATE_GENERATE_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ACCOUNTS, PERSISTENCE & ABUSE CONTROL (Supabase)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create a free project at https://supabase.com, then from
# Project Settings -> API copy: the Project URL, the anon/public key, and the
# service_role key (secret — server only, NEVER ship to the browser).
#
# Add these to .dev.vars for local dev. Note the two VITE_* copies: those are
# the ONLY Supabase values that reach the browser (URL + anon key are safe to
# expose; the service_role key must never be prefixed with VITE_).
#
#      SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
#      SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
#      SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key   # server-only secret
#      VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
#      VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
#
# Daily usage caps (abuse / bankruptcy protection). Optional — sane defaults
# apply if unset. Per-user is the free-tier meter; global is the hard spend cap
# across ALL users for one day, after which every AI route returns 429.
#
#      SLATE_DAILY_USER_LIMIT=400       # AI calls per user per day
#      SLATE_DAILY_GLOBAL_LIMIT=20000   # AI calls across all users per day
#
# PRODUCTION — set each server secret once with wrangler (VITE_* ones are build
# -time and must be present when you run `npm run build`, e.g. in CI env):
#
#      npx wrangler secret put SUPABASE_URL
#      npx wrangler secret put SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#      npx wrangler secret put SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BOT WALL (Cloudflare Turnstile) — optional, gated by env
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Free widget at https://dash.cloudflare.com -> Turnstile. Create a widget to
# get a Site key (public) and Secret key. Then in the Supabase Dashboard ->
# Authentication -> Attack Protection, enable CAPTCHA, choose Turnstile, and
# paste the Secret key. Supabase then rejects any signup/login whose captcha
# token is missing or invalid — walling bots out of account creation, which
# (since AI requires login) walls them out of your spend.
#
# The login form only renders the widget when this is set, so the app runs fine
# without it:
#
#      VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=your-turnstile-site-key
